When a user does a safety audit, the specific location gets geotagged. They input data on a scale of 0-3 for the parameters lighting, walk path, security, public transport, visibility, openness, people and gender usage. There is also an additional parameter, feeling, which rates the user’s perception of safety in that place. This data is used to create the safety score of a place.

The Safety Score is calculated based on the data collected from both our apps My Safetipin and Safetipin Nite. The data from My Safetipin is crowdsourced and is analysed based on the 8 parameters- lighting, walk path, security, people, gender, openness, visibility and public transport. Each parameter is given a weight and using this, the score is calculated out of 10.\10 The Safety Score is the value that can be seen on the map when the user opens the app. You can also see the safety score of other places either by searching in the search box or by moving the pin on the map.

The safety score helps you in understanding the safety of a place based on the physical and social parameters. You can use the safety score to make safer decisions about your travel and stay. The safety score is also used in the safest route feature and for providing accurate notifications in the tracking feature.

The tracking feature can be enabled by a user to let their selected friends and family know about their location in case they are traveling alone or are feeling unsafe. This feature can be started from the tracking icon on the home screen (on the top right) or from the safest route screen. If it is from the safest route screen, then the route will show on the tracking screen and any deviations from that will send a notification to all the people tracking the user. They will also get notifications if you are in an area of a low safety score or if you have not moved for over 10 minutes.

Safetipin is a map-based mobile application, which works towards making streets and public spaces safer by providing safety related information based on physical and social infrastructure parameters. Safetipin aims to build a world where everyone can move around without fear, specially women. Users can share their experience of a place or a city via the Safety Audit feature in the app as well as use this data to understand their neighborhood or city better. The My Safetipin app can be used to make safer decisions about your travel and stay!

Why is Safetipin track better than the tracking feature of Google maps?

The most important feature of Safetipin tracking, is that it sends the person tracking you with notifications in case something is not quite right. We provide notifications for the following- \10 1 If the person being tracked is in an area with a safety score less than 2 \10 2 If the person being tracked has not moved in 10 minutes\10 3 If the person diverts from the route (if one is selected from the safest route feature)\10
